      "description": "Offering a mechanically robust 987.2 Cayman S featuring the 3.4L flat-six with Direct Fuel Injection (DFI) and a 6-speed manual transaxle. This mid-engine chassis provides exceptional polar moment of inertia, resulting in neutral handling and precise turn-in. The engine exhibits strong compression across all cylinders with no signs of AOS failure or IMS concerns relevant to older blocks. Recent service includes new spark plugs, ignition coils, and a brake fluid flush using high-boiling-point synthetic. The suspension geometry remains true, and the hydraulic steering rack provides the communicative feedback missing from modern EPS systems. While the exterior shows minor stone chips from spirited use, the drivetrain is in peak operational form.",
